    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 7 Engine Service Manual - Exhaust Gas Recirculating (EGR) System -
        Installation - Exhaust Gas Recirculating (EGR) Cooler
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s04.4.2" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="10">
        <title>Exhaust Gas Recirculating (EGR) Cooler</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para id="s04.4.2.ref1">To prevent engine damage, hand torque all nuts and bolts of EGR system. EGR
                    hardware has a special high-temperature coating which will be damaged by air tools.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f3450004024" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM17/M17112.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>EGR cooler assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">EGR cooler clamp (3)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">EGR top bracket</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">EGR cooler bracket</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">EGR cooler</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place EGR cooler in EGR cooler bracket.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install EGR top bracket on EGR cooler.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Do not tighten EGR cooler clamps at this time.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosely install three new EGR cooler clamps.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Make sure two #10 washers are present on turbocharger stud bolts.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position new gaskets and install EGR cooler to engine.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450004025" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figm17/M17107.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>EGR cooler outlet bolts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install two M8 x 20 EGR cooler outlet bolts. Tighten bolts to
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_105.xml" xrefid="s04.t1">special torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s04.t1"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450004026" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figm17/M17108.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>EGR cooler inlet bolts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install three new M8 x 27 EGR cooler inlet bolts. Tighten bolts to
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_343.xml" xrefid="s19.t1">standard torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s19.t1"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450004027" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figm17/M17109.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>EGR cooler bracket bolts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosely install four M10 x 50 EGR cooler bracket bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten three EGR cooler clamps as follows:</para>
            <seqlist>
                <item>
                    <para>Tighten clamps to 10 N&#183;m (89 lbf&#183;in).</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Back out clamps two full turns.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Re-tighten clamps to 8 N&#183;m (71 lbf&#183;in).</para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten four M10 x 50 EGR cooler bracket bolts to
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_343.xml" xrefid="s19.t1">standard torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s19.t1"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450004028" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figm17/M17111.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>EGR top bracket nuts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install two M10 x 1.5 EGR top bracket nuts. Tighten nuts to
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_105.xml" xrefid="s04.t1">special torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s04.t1"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install new seals on EGR coolant supply and EGR coolant return tubes.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect EGR coolant supply and EGR coolant return tubes to EGR cooler and front crankcase
                cover.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450004029" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figm17/M17106.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>EGR coolant supply and EGR coolant return tube bolts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install EGR coolant supply and EGR coolant return tube bolts. Tighten bolts to
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_343.xml" xrefid="s19.t1">standard torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s19.t1"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450004030" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM17/M17105.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Fan drive pulley</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 x 20 bolts (6)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fan drive pulley</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Use a holding device to lock fan drive pulley when installing bolts.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install fan drive pulley and six M8 x 20 bolts. Tighten bolts to
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_343.xml" xrefid="s19.t1">standard torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s19.t1"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450004031" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM17/M17104.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Coolant hose clamps</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten four coolant hose clamps to
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_105.xml" xrefid="s04.t1">special torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s04.t1"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450004032" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM15/M15109.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Charging circuit bridge</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M6 x 16 bolt and nut (1)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Charging circuit bridge</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M6 nut (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 nut (1)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide charging circuit bridge under wiring harness and onto two right valve cover stud
                bolts. Install two M6 nuts and tighten to
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_343.xml" xrefid="s19.t1">standard torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s19.t1"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position charging circuit bridge bracket onto turbo oil inlet flange stud bolt. Install M8
                nut and tighten to
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_343.xml" xrefid="s19.t1">standard torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s19.t1"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Secure charging circuit bridge to Electronic Control Module (ECM) support with M6&#160;x&#160;16
                bolt and nut. Tighten to
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_343.xml" xrefid="s19.t1">standard torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s19.t1"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450004033" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM15/M15108.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Breather tube</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Breather tube</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Breather hose clamps (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M6 nut</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect breather tube hose to breather and tighten hose clamp.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect breather tube to turbo air inlet duct and tighten hose clamp.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect breather tube clamp to charging circuit bridge and secure with M6 nut. Tighten nut
                to
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_343.xml" xrefid="s19.t1">standard torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s19.t1"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
